plantContents.name: Bonsai
plantContents.description: Bonsai is a Japanese art form using cultivation techniques to produce small trees in containers that mimic the shape and scale of full size trees.

plantContents.name: Aloe Vera
plantContents.description: Aloe vera is a succulent plant species of the genus Aloe. An evergreen perennial, it originates from the Arabian Peninsula, but grows wild in tropical, semi-tropical, and arid climates around the world.

plantContents.name: Snake Plant
plantContents.description: The snake plant, also known as mother-in-law's tongue or Saint George's sword, is a flowering plant species in the family Asparagaceae, native to tropical West Africa.
